BREAST-COMPOSITION: fibro fatty and glandular breast parenchyma (ACR B).
FINDINGS: A small, well-defined irregular soft opacity with spiculated margins is seen in the upper outer quadrant of the breast. This finding suggests a low suspicion for malignancy (BIRADS 4A). No abnormal microcalcifications are observed. The overlying skin and nipple appear normal. Pectoral muscle and axillary lymph nodes show no significant abnormalities.
